<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,229,775]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,349,375]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</emphasis>
The affinities of this species have been erroneously interpreted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaszab, Z." box="[1110,1285,349,375]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="144 - 204" refId="ref23584" refString="Kaszab, Z. (1983) Insects of Saudi Arabia. Coleoptera: Fam. Meloidae - A synopsis of the Arabian Meloidae. Fauna of Saudi Arabia, 5, 144 - 204." type="journal article" year="1983">Kaszab (1983)</bibRefCitation>
, who related it to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[204,358,389,414]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunnipes">
<emphasis box="[204,358,389,414]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">H. brunnipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In fact, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bologna &amp; Turco" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Kaszab" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[463,699,389,414]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudobrunnipes">
<emphasis box="[463,699,389,414]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">H. pseudobrunnipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has the mesosternum (
<figureCitation box="[1023,1108,389,415]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[286,1319,184,1729]" captionTargetId="figure-90@27.[225,1359,152,1762]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Hycleus dunalis n. sp. (16–17) 16. right elytron; 17. mesosternal sclerites. Hycleus pseudobrunnipes (Kaszab) (18–19) 18. mesosternal sclerites; 19. male genitalia, lateral view. Hycleus fraudulentus n.sp. (20–21). 20. right elytron; 21. mesosternal sclerites. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5103312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5103312/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) of 
<emphasis box="[1156,1324,389,414]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Mesogorbatus</emphasis>
- 
<typeStatus box="[1332,1387,389,415]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">type</typeStatus>
, but the male genitalia, never described before (
<figureCitation box="[655,742,429,455]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–21" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[286,1319,184,1729]" captionTargetId="figure-90@27.[225,1359,152,1762]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 16–21. Hycleus dunalis n. sp. (16–17) 16. right elytron; 17. mesosternal sclerites. Hycleus pseudobrunnipes (Kaszab) (18–19) 18. mesosternal sclerites; 19. male genitalia, lateral view. Hycleus fraudulentus n.sp. (20–21). 20. right elytron; 21. mesosternal sclerites. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5103312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5103312/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
), have the same structure as that of the group of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Marseul" baseAuthorityYear="1870" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quatuordecimsignatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">H. quatuordecimsignatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pardo Alcaide, A." box="[517,756,469,495]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="572 - 588" refId="ref23898" refString="Pardo Alcaide, A. (1963) Coleopteres Meloides recoltes par M. J. Mateu dans l'Ennedi et au Tchad. Etudes sur les Meloidae, XII, Bulletin de l'Institut fondamental de l'Afrique Noire, (A) 25, 572 - 588." type="journal article" year="1963">Pardo Alcaide 1963</bibRefCitation>
, and by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruiz, J. L." box="[860,988,469,495]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="95 - 100" refId="ref24266" refString="Ruiz, J. L. (2004) Morfologia y distribucion de Hycleus rungsi (Peyerimhoff, 1935), un endemismo de Marruecos meridional (Coleoptera, Meloidae). Boletin de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa, 34, 95 - 100." type="journal article" year="2004">Ruiz 2004</bibRefCitation>
), with two aedeagus hooks, the distal one very small, instead of a single distal hook as in the group of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[933,1088,509,534]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunnipes">
<emphasis box="[933,1088,509,534]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">H. brunnipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The reduction in length and thickness of the ventral lobe of the claws, sets apart this species within the group; this claw reduction is common to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bologna &amp; Turco" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Marseul" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[244,390,589,614]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gratiosus">
<emphasis box="[244,390,589,614]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">H. gratiosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(in this species the reduction is extreme), whose position is uncertain because the male genitalia are unknown. Therefore the group of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Marseul" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[698,993,629,654]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quatuordecimsignatus">
<emphasis box="[698,993,629,654]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">H. quatuordecimsignatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes at least four Saharo-Arabian species (see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Ruiz, J. L." box="[353,481,669,695]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="95 - 100" refId="ref24266" refString="Ruiz, J. L. (2004) Morfologia y distribucion de Hycleus rungsi (Peyerimhoff, 1935), un endemismo de Marruecos meridional (Coleoptera, Meloidae). Boletin de la Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa, 34, 95 - 100." type="journal article" year="2004">Ruiz 2004</bibRefCitation>
): two endemic to the 
<collectingCountry box="[735,921,669,695]" name="Western Sahara" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Western Sahara</collectingCountry>
, namely 
<taxonomicName authority="(Peyerimhoff, 1935)" baseAuthorityName="Peyerimhoff" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[1027,1385,669,695]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rungsi">
<emphasis box="[1027,1139,669,694]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">H. rungsi</emphasis>
(Peyerimhoff, 1935)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Chobaut, 1901)" baseAuthorityName="Chobaut" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[151,502,709,735]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saharicus">
<emphasis box="[151,300,709,734]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">H. saharicus</emphasis>
(Chobaut, 1901)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="(Marseul, 1870)" baseAuthorityName="Marseul" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[514,1007,709,735]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quatuordecimsignatus">
<emphasis box="[514,808,709,734]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">H. quatuordecimsignatus</emphasis>
(Marseul, 1870)
</taxonomicName>
, widely distributed from 
<collectingCountry box="[1301,1406,709,735]" name="Morocco" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Morocco</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[151,224,749,775]" name="Egypt" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Egypt</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[236,301,749,775]" name="Israel" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Israel</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[357,439,749,775]" name="Jordan" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Jordan</collectingCountry>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kaszab, 1983)" authorityName="Bologna &amp; Turco" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Kaszab" baseAuthorityYear="1983" box="[451,873,749,775]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudobrunnipes">
<emphasis box="[451,687,749,774]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">H. pseudobrunnipes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kaszab, Z." box="[703,865,749,775]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="144 - 204" refId="ref23584" refString="Kaszab, Z. (1983) Insects of Saudi Arabia. Coleoptera: Fam. Meloidae - A synopsis of the Arabian Meloidae. Fauna of Saudi Arabia, 5, 144 - 204." type="journal article" year="1983">Kaszab, 1983</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
endemic to the Arabian Peninsula.
</paragraph>
